(Import [(btio ([(Information Curation)] Decision [|Deployed Spirit can REMOVE intent records, superseding the append-only/flag-only constraint. Clean the log by removing (1) stale records superseded by a newer record/INTENT.md/skill that absorbs their substance, and (2) working orders that fail the after-the-task test. Every change needs a justifying psyche statement (a deletion is justified by e.g. a changed mind, no replacement arrow required); removal is psyche-authorized and conservative — when removability is uncertain, flag rather than remove, since over-removal beats under-removal.|] High VeryHigh Zero [spirit intent-log])) (rvnf ([(Information Curation)] Correction [Agents must not respond to Spirit overcapture by avoiding Spirit entirely; the correct discipline is to apply the conservative capture gate and use Spirit only for explicit durable decisions, principles, corrections, clarifications, and constraints.] VeryHigh Minimum Zero [spirit capture-gate])) (icpa ([(Information Curation)] Principle [Spirit's overriding design goal is to be maximally clutter-free, a curated pristine intent store rather than a capture-everything log] High Minimum Zero [spirit])) (tfpd ([(Information Curation)] Principle [The guardian judges a proposed intent change against the actual verbatim words of the psyche and their context, not only against existing records. A bare affirmation like yes or okay must travel with the statement it answered] High VeryHigh Zero [spirit intent-log guardian])) (0r17 ([(Information Curation)] Decision [|Reports are a small load-bearing set, not an accumulating archive; history lives in jj/git. Context maintenance reduces report count without losing information by agglomerating per topic: multiple reports become one Refresh report (the Capital variant tag after the number) preserving un-contradicted, un-superseded substance in better form; source reports are then deleted with the Refresh report as landing witness.|] High High Zero [reports refresh context-maintenance])) (6z6t ([(Information Curation)] Correction [Agglomerating repeated or related intent preserves source provenance and may preserve accumulated importance through weight where that axis exists, but does not automatically raise certainty; certainty rises only when the synthesized statement is itself better supported or stated with higher confidence.] High Medium Zero [spirit agglomeration certainty])) (ek8w ([(Information Curation)] Decision [Intent agglomeration and refresh is triggered by an automated auditor that auto-proposes refreshes; the psyche confirms the retire of source records. Automated discovery with human-gated removal, preserving the conservative over-removal-is-worse discipline.] Medium Minimum Zero [auditor spirit agglomeration])) (tf2o ([(Information Curation)] Principle [Intent refresh and agglomeration is primarily agent behavior trained through a skill, not engine logic: agents learn how to refresh many related intents into fewer stronger records. The only supporting code is the relations field; the refreshing judgment lives in agent behavior and the intent-maintenance skill.] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit agglomeration intent-maintenance-skill])) (mi6m ([(Information Curation)] Principle [Closing duplicate beads must preserve all information from the closed bead; competing design ideas are kept so agents in those fields can compare and essay them] Medium Minimum Zero [beads])) (tbg6 ([(Information Curation)] Principle [Intent gaps are filled by cross-pollinating patterns found elsewhere in the intent — when one area of intent lacks a clear design, look for an analogous pattern already established in another area and project it onto the gap. Surfaces broken or implicit conventions and turns them into stated principles. Used during intent-clarity audits of recent work.] Medium Minimum Zero [intent-log intent-clarity-audit])) (yenl ([(Information Curation)] Clarification [|For a prompt addressing multiple lanes, the default capturer is the first responder — in practice the operator (Codex), faster than the designer (Claude) — who writes the Spirit entry; the slower lane then gap-checks and gap-fills only a genuine omission rather than writing a parallel entry. Per psyche 2026-06-05.|] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit operator designer capture-gate])) (7hrd ([(Technology (Software Data))] Correction [|The Spirit intent log holds only durable psyche statements (Decision/Principle/Correction/Clarification/Constraint) that outlive any single task. Test: would the record still guide after its task is done? Working orders (create-report, dispatch-subagent, audit-X, integrate-branches) are task state; from a task prompt capture only the durable intent within it. A mis-logged working order is flagged as a capture error, not deleted.|] VeryHigh High Zero [spirit intent-log working-orders])) (j6r4 ([(Technology (Software Data))] Principle [Spirit certainty follows an honest 8-level magnitude rubric. Maximum only for foundational invariants and hard overrides that are repeatedly ratified and stable. VeryHigh for ratified decisions clearly in force. High for solid decisions with minor open edges. Medium for working decisions and design directions still settling, which is the honest home for most ticks agents used to reflexively mark Maximum. Low and VeryLow for leans, proposals, and explicitly-pending-information. Minimum for weak tentative signal. Zero for removal candidates. Certainty is assigned deliberately, never reflexively. *validation*] High VeryHigh Zero [spirit certainty certainty-rubric])) (kasm ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [|Spirit capture is a blocking guardian gate, not an advisory check: the guardian vets and admits a proposed record before capture succeeds, resolving or refusing duplicates, contradictions, compounds, and non-intent at the door. An entry and the new referents it introduces are decided as one atomic accept/reject, so no orphan referent survives a refused entry;