The Spirit RecordQuery composes filter dimensions: TopicSelection (multi-topic, partial=any-of or full=all-of, plus topic-catalog queries), optional Kind, CertaintySelection (filter by certainty/magnitude to select e.g. removal candidates), and a first-class RecencySelection (Any, Newest N, Since identifier/timestamp, Window range). Also support numeric-identifier lookup (exact and ranges), qualitative depth requests (deeper/very-deep) instead of exact counts, public-only/private-only shortcut verbs, and an explicit privacy-query subtype exposing at-most/equal/at-least selectors while normal queries stay Zero-only.|] Medium Low Zero [spirit query record-query recency-selection topic-selection privacy-query])) (m3eg ([(Technology (Software Data))] Principle [|The cloud daemon starts almost-stateless and caches last-known-state of queried provider (Cloudflare) resources; cache loss is acceptable because the provider is the source of truth. The first cache is runtime/volatile (in-memory), provider-backed and possibly lossy; persistent storage is deferred until state worth preserving emerges.|] Medium Low Zero [cloud-daemon cache cloudflare])) (lvy9 ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [|Real-time streaming is a new Signal capability (working name signal-real-time): it is Signal, not Sema, and its storage format is open (likely a native real-time format rather than Sema).|] Low Low Zero [signal-real-time signal sema stream-processing])) (3don ([(Technology (Software Data))] Constraint [Schema source lowering rejects duplicate declarations for the same type name: when an inline declaration and another inline or trailing namespace declaration both introduce a name, it is an error, not an order-dependent override or merge.] High Low Zero [schema schema-lowering topic])) (29ed ([(Technology (Software Data))] Constraint [A registered but undelegated domain name returns a typed no-records result.] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit domain query])) (7y8w ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Principle [|NOTA's bracket-only string form makes any NOTA expression embedding-safe and escape-free inside every double-quote host (JSON, Rust raw strings, Nix, YAML, TOML, shell args, HTTP bodies, DB columns, env vars, XML attrs): NOTA never emits a double-quote. NOTA is the carrier; the schema at each embedding site supplies meaning.|] VeryHigh Medium Zero [nota schema])) (vr32 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [|NOTA structs are positional: position plus the read-time schema encodes meaning, no field-name tags. Plain PascalCase tokens are unit variants; parenthesized variants carry data. Every field is always present, with explicit None for an optional value (Spirit privacy comes from public/private shorthand that lowers to the full record, not omitted fields).|] VeryHigh Medium Zero [nota schema spirit])) (bsrv ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Constraint [NOTA spells unspaced multi-word string atoms in camelCase like theSouthField, mirroring PascalCase for type variants, never kebab-case] High High Zero [nota])) (0dsr ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Constraint [|NOTA string delimiters are required only for strings with spaces or forbidden symbols; bare-eligible strings (topic names, symbol-safe schema and type names) stay bare atoms.|] High Minimum Zero [nota schema])) (3qjw ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [The four-character bracket-pipe delimiter is for pretty indented multiline string blocks with common indentation stripped on parse, not the ordinary inline delimiter. Keep one pipe-text shape and escape literal close-marker text rather than widening fences.] Medium Minimum Zero [nota])) (ghw7 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [|The NOTA brace {} is a strict key-value map: every entry is exactly a key plus a value, no single-token entries. Key-value-ness is low-level NOTA structure (macros may consume it at schema positions). Keys form a typed enum where case plus sigil selects the variant and dispatches the value type. Namespace body is {TypeName TypeDefinition}; struct body is {fieldName TypeRef}; derived names use a value-side marker like (Derive).|] High High Zero [nota schema])) (voa8 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [|Square brackets are NOTA's raw vector container delimiter, not the schema syntax for declaring a Vec; declare a vector type with an explicit parenthesized typed object (Vec of X). At a typed position expecting String or a string newtype, bracket content reads as string data (a string is a vector of characters), so [] is not always a vector.|] Medium Minimum Zero [nota schema])) (sqx6 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [|Gap-fill from forwarded designer exchange confirmed by psyche: NOTA owns raw structure and serialization shapes, plus the value literal None with present values as (Some x). Schema owns the entire type-name vocabulary: scalars such as String, Integer, Boolean, and future scalar names, and composites such as Vec, Optional, Map, and future composite names. Moving only composites to Schema while leaving scalar type names in NOTA is inconsistent; all type-name keywords belong to Schema.|] High Minimum Zero [nota schema])) (yp29 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [|schema-next needs a Bytes primitive (ideally fixed-size byte arrays) beyond String/Integer/Boolean/Path, so binary values (BLS keys, signatures, digests, fingerprints, nonces) type as bytes. It also needs a hash-identifier type whose value is bytes but whose NOTA projection is a canonical short string code, generalizing the 12-byte base36 RecordIdentifier.|] Medium Minimum Zero [schema-next nota record-identifier])) (qmbf ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Decision [|When a data-carrying variant's payload is a single-use enum, inline it as a bracket list at the variant position — (Busy [DatabaseOverloaded ResourceDisconnected OtherReason]) — rather than naming an enum and wrapping. Name it separately when reused, semantically independent, large (10+ variants), or part of a stable cross-component contract.|] High Minimum Zero [nota schema])) (p8sq ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Clarification [|A .schema file reads in a known Schema context: its root struct type is implied by the extension/filename (like Rust modules), so fields appear positionally with no outer wrapper. The root holds a key-value map of datatype names to raw NOTA objects, first field the imports/exports namespace (brace map) then input/output struct(s) in square brackets, combinable. Reading needs both meta-schema and concrete schema through the same self-describing format; authored data files prefer typed NOTA whose filename defines the root type.|] Medium Minimum Zero [schema nota])) (sfwv ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Clarification [|The resolved assembled-schema artifact is the Asschema (.asschema) file: pure NOTA holding fully resolved enum and struct definitions with no remaining macros, read against the known Asschema root struct positionally with no outer wrapper. Human-readable debug output is not .asschema and must be named as a witness.|] Medium Minimum Zero [asschema nota schema])) (9uje ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Clarification [|Schema headers are ordered enum-root declarations (a vector of ordered enum variants), not namespace vectors. Assembled root syntax carries Input and Output bodies directly in their known positions or via a real common enum object, never wrapped in meaningless one-field structs added to satisfy vector syntax.|] Medium Minimum Zero [schema nota])) (vqbt ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [|Plural record replies (e.g. RecordsObserved) expose the vector directly in the signal tree rather than wrapping it in a single-field record that nests delimiters before the vector.|] Low Minimum Zero [nota signal-tree records-observed])) (opbj ([(Technology (Software (Data Migration)))] Decision [Re-